abstract: Long before a shooting and protests in Ferguson, Mo., focused America’s attention on how the police treat black men, Los Angeles was a byword for police brutality and racism.
snippet: Long before a shooting and protests in Ferguson, Mo., focused America’s attention on how the police treat black men, Los Angeles was a byword for police brutality and racism.
lead_paragraph: LOS ANGELES — John Weber was rummaging through old boxes the other day, looking for memories, when he found a bunch of old baseball and flag football trophies. He has kept other things, too, like a neatly pressed R.O.T.C. uniform, a reminder that he once hoped to steer his son, Anthony, to the Army and away from the streets.

abstract: Investigators believe a man in Arizona was distributing performance-enhancing drugs on a global scale, yet no charges have been filed. His clientele included pro athletes.
snippet: Investigators believe a man in Arizona was distributing performance-enhancing drugs on a global scale, yet no charges have been filed. His clientele included pro athletes.
lead_paragraph: On Aug. 25, 2015, a Swiss postal inspector reached into the river of 300,000 parcels that pour into that nation every day and, for a routine inspection, plucked out two packages arriving from Arizona. Inspectors unwrapped them and found serried rows of bottles.

abstract: I chased patterns where there were none, but I saw one that was very real: This was not the only relationship my mental illness would detonate.

lead_paragraph: “You must really love that song,” my mother says, and for a moment my heart stops.

headline_main: How I Finally Kicked My O.C.D.

abstract: And other possibly distressing lessons from the recent fashion season.
snippet: And other possibly distressing lessons from the recent fashion season.
lead_paragraph: I have spent the last month trapped in a wrinkle in time. Not the film, mind you, though that was quite the fashion moment, and not the book. Rather, sitting by the runways, hour after hour, day after day, city after city between Feb. 7 and March 7, I could feel myself slipping further down a wormhole into the past. One moment it was 2018; the next it was 1981 (or ’85, or ’88).

abstract: There’s a gender gap when it comes to earning, or wanting to earn, at the highest levels.

lead_paragraph: Women are running for political office in record numbers this year. They are challenging the sexual status quo from Hollywood to corporate offices, pursuing power as seldom before.
